caption: We've stopped in here a couple of times now when we've been meandering the quarter in the evening. Staff is very polite, the bar comfortable and relaxed. It's definitely more a neighborhood bar than a lot of places down there... which is exactly how we prefer it.

So I travel to New Orleans at least once a year and this is a place that I usually visit at least once each trip. However after today I will no longer be visiting Molly's. During my last and final visit the bartender was very unattentive to my party so I decided not to leave a tip on the bill. As I was walking towards the door the bartender took the opportunity to yell "thanks for the tip" while giving me a dirty look. If the owner/manger of the business happens to read this know that the bartender was serving at approximately 1pm on Monday July 2nd, 2018 and was the only bartender at the bar.

First time I strolled in was night after Stevie Ray Vaughn died. It was, as the owner said, "Tuesday every drunk in town is downing dollar drinks in my bar, Dollar Drink Night." I think those days are but a memory, but the impression that made on me has made Molly's a repeat destination every time I've come through NOLA since. Great atmosphere, drinks with elbow, and a most definite separate break from the tourist traps of the Square. Highly recommended!!!

Great selection of whiskys and Guinness on tap. Usually friendly and knowledgeable bar staff. And a surprisingly clean restroom for its location. They run a tight ship at Mollys. Also a great jukebox, not a streaming one.

We stumbled into Molly's our second night here. Great Irish pub just off Bourbon street with good, cheap, drinks. The bartenders the night we were there rocked. Jenna and Pam. If you girls read this, show it to your boss. They were friendly, and made the experience. So many of the bars in the quarter get by on reputation and the staff sometimes treat you like you're lucky to be served. They forget who pays the bills. If you are in the area, and enjoy a good pint of Guinness, by all means go here...
